results.deck: Atlus is a Japanese game developer and publisher.
results.description:
Overview

Atlus is a developer based in Tokyo. They are best known for the RPG franchise Shin Megami Tensei. The very first game in the Megami Tensei franchise was on the Famicom and published by Namco. After the release of Megami Tensei II, also on the Famicom, members such as Cozy Okada and Kazuma Kaneko formed Atlus, with their first release Shin Megami Tensei for the Super Famicom. They were bought by Takara in 2003 which would be their owners until 2006 when Index Holding bought Atlus.

Despite the buy outs Atlus would stay an independent company until 2010, when Index Holdings completely took over control of Atlus. This caused unrest with the fans, however Shinichi Suzuki, CEO of Atlus stated that

"Atlus will continue to provide the finest quality game experiences possible"

The official mascot of Atlus is Jack Frost from the Shin Megami Tensei franchise.
